TOKYO -LRB- AP -RRB- A fairly strong earthquake with preliminary magnitude of 6.2 shook much of northern Japan Saturday , the Central Meteorological Agency reported .
The quake that struck at 5:47 p.m. -LRB- 0847 GMT -RRB- was centered 70 kilometers -LRB- 44 miles -RRB- under the sea off Nemuro on the eastern tip of the northern main island of Hokkaido , the agency said .
No damage or injuries were reported immediately .
The agency said the intensity of the quake measured four on the Japanese scale of seven in Kushiro , 890 kilometers -LRB- 560 miles -RRB- northeast of Tokyo , and three at nearby Nemuro .
The Japanese scale shows intensity of earthquakes at difference locations , and is not convertable into magnitude .
The devastating earthquake that hit the Kobe area in western Japan Tuesday had a preliminary magnitude of 7.2 and measured seven on the Japanese scale .
The epicenter of that quake was right under populated areas .
The agency said there was no danger of tsunami , or tidal waves , from the Hokkaido quake .
